<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00088</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT GRANTING UNIVERSAL SOCIAL PENSION TO SENIOR CITIZENS, FURTHER AMENDING REPUBLIC ACT NO. 7432, AS AMENDED BY RA 9994, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE ꞌEXPANDED SENIOR CITIZENS ACT OF 2010ꞌ</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to grant Social Pension to ALL SENIOR CITIZENS a monthly stipend amounting to a minimum of One Thousand Pesos (Php1,000.00) to augment their daily subsistence and other medical needs,  provided that such senior citizen does not receive a pension of more than Three Thousand Five Hundred Pesos (Php3,500.00) from the GSIS, the SSS, and other public or private social protection system.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GARBIN, ALFREDO JR. A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Salceda (000 2019-08-13)</td><td>2. Olivarez (000 2019-09-04)</td><tr><td>3. Lacson-Noel (000 2019-10-17)</td><td>4. Belmonte (000 2020-06-17)</td><tr><td>5. Espina (000 2020-06-17)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON SENIOR CITIZENS ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>